Loiseau, Pernod, Schneider, Vivendi: French Equity Preview

-- B y   G r e g o r y   V i s c u s i   a n d   M a r k   D e e n
-- 
2011-04-05T04:00:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-04/loiseau-pernod-schneider-vivendi-french-equity-preview.html
The following companies’ shares may
be active in Paris. Stock symbols are in parentheses after
company names and prices are from the last close.  France ’s  CAC 40 Index (CAC)  fell 0.3 percent to 4,042.92. The
broader SBF 120 fell 0.1 percent to 3,036.45.  Bernard Loiseau SA (BLOI)  : The restaurant company said
it earned 448,000 euros ($637,000) last year after posting a
loss in 2009. The shares fell 2.1 percent to 4.63 euros.  Pernod Ricard SA (RI FP): The liquor company said it sold
back a 1 percent stake in Suntory Holdings Ltd. to the Japanese
brewer, for about 4.66 billion yen ($55.5 million) in cash.
Pernod shares fell 0.2 percent to 65.87 euros.  Schneider Electric SA (SU)  : The electrical equipment
maker paid an undisclosed sum for Lee Technologies, an equipment
provider for data centers based in Fairfax, Virginia with sales
of about $140 million in 2010. The shares fell less than 0.1
percent to 123.15 euros.  Vivendi SA (VIV)  : The communications company’s complete
takeover of mobile-phone operator SFR will add about 600 million
euros in adjusted net income in each of 2012 and 2013, Chief
Executive Officer Jean-Bernard Levy said on a conference call.
The shares gained 0.6 percent to 20.64 euros.  To contact the reporters on this story:
